  "data": {
    "title": "BugHerd: Get Client Feedback That Actually Makes Sense",
    "excerpt": "BugHerd lets clients point, click, and comment on live websites—no more confusing emails. Try BugHerd and streamline your feedback process today.",
    "featured_image": {
      "$media": {
        "url": "https://tonyciencia.com/blog/bugherd-new-features.jpg",
        "alt": "BugHerd: Get Client Feedback That Actually Makes Sense",
        "filename": "bugherd-new-features.jpg"
      }
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you've ever tried to collect website feedback from clients through email threads, screenshots pasted into Word docs, or vague Slack messages like \"that thing on the right looks off,\" you know the pain. Details get lost. Context disappears. Developers waste hours playing detective.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "BugHerd eliminates all of that. It lets clients and stakeholders leave feedback directly on a live website by simply pointing, clicking, and typing a comment. BugHerd automatically captures a screenshot, records the browser version, screen resolution, operating system, and even the exact element being referenced—then packages everything into a clean task your team can act on.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've been using BugHerd for a few months now, and honestly, it's one of those tools that makes you wonder how you ever managed without it. Here's what's new, what I love, and why you should give it a spin.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://partners.bugherd.com/tj7d6g9xsdd0"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Check out BugHerd here",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How BugHerd Works (It's Stupidly Simple)",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The magic of BugHerd is that it requires zero technical skill from your clients. No browser extensions. No training sessions. No \"please fill out this Jira ticket.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's the flow:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. You install a small JavaScript snippet on your website (takes about 2 minutes).",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. You invite clients or team members via email.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. They visit the live site, click on any element, and leave a comment in the sidebar.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. BugHerd grabs a screenshot, pins the comment to the exact spot, and captures all the technical metadata automatically.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. The feedback appears as a task in your BugHerd kanban board, ready to assign and track.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "That's it. My client Sarah, who once described herself as \"not a tech person,\" left 14 comments in her first session without a single question. She told me it felt like \"leaving sticky notes on a real page.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-bugherd"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want a deeper walkthrough, here's a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "step-by-step tutorial on how to use BugHerd",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "New and Highlighted Features Worth Knowing",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "BugHerd keeps rolling out improvements, and a few recent ones have genuinely leveled up my workflow:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Screenshot and screen recording capture.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " When a client leaves feedback, BugHerd now grabs a full screenshot of the page at that exact moment. You can even ask clients to record a short video clip walking through the issue. No more \"I can't reproduce it\" back-and-forth.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Kanban board with drag-and-drop task management.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Every piece of feedback becomes a task you can drag between columns—Backlog, In Progress, Done, whatever you customize. I've ditched my separate project management tool for website review phases entirely. It's all inside BugHerd now.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Browser and environment metadata.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Each comment automatically includes the browser, OS, screen resolution, and URL. When a client says \"the button doesn't work,\" you already know they're on Safari 17 on a MacBook Air at 1440×900. That context alone saves my developer an hour per sprint.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Guest access with no login required.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Clients can leave feedback without creating a BugHerd account. You send them a link, they click, they comment. This alone has doubled the speed of feedback cycles on my last three projects.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/bugherd-use-cases"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Integrations with Jira, Asana, Slack, and GitHub.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " BugHerd tasks sync directly into the tools your team already uses. Feedback flows in, tasks flow out, and nobody has to copy-paste anything. Learn more about how it fits with other platforms in this ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "BugHerd use cases guide",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Custom fields and tags.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " You can add priority levels, labels, and custom fields to each task. I tag feedback by page (\"Homepage,\" \"Pricing,\" \"Blog\") so my team can batch similar fixes together.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://partners.bugherd.com/tj7d6g9xsdd0"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "See all BugHerd features in action",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Why I Prefer BugHerd Over Other Feedback Methods",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've tried a lot of approaches over the years. Google Docs with annotated screenshots. Loom videos with timestamps. Trello boards where clients paste screenshots manually. Each one had the same problem: the feedback was disconnected from the actual website.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "BugHerd solves this by anchoring every comment to a specific element on a specific page at a specific moment. There's no ambiguity. When my developer opens a task, they see exactly what the client saw, where they clicked, and what they said. No translation layer needed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Compared to tools like Marker.io or Usersnap, BugHerd stands out for its simplicity. Clients genuinely enjoy using it. The sidebar is intuitive. The kanban board is built in. And the price point is accessible for freelancers and small agencies alike.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-bugherd"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you're weighing your options, here's a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "detailed comparison of why to choose BugHerd",
            "marks": [
              "l4"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Who BugHerd Is Ideal For",
