        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The common thread? Anyone who needs to communicate about a website and wants that communication to be precise, visual, and organized.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Real-World Tips From My Workflow",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After a few months with BugHerd, I've picked up some habits that make the tool even more effective:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Set up the kanban columns to match your actual process.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " I use: \"New Feedback,\" \"Needs Clarification,\" \"In Development,\" \"Ready for Review,\" and \"Done.\" It mirrors how my team actually works.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use the browser extension for internal reviews.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " BugHerd has a browser extension that lets you leave feedback on any site, not just ones where you've installed the snippet. I use it when reviewing third-party landing pages or competitor sites.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Create a short client onboarding doc.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " One page with screenshots showing how to leave feedback. I include it in every project kickoff email. It takes 5 minutes to write and saves hours of confusion.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Batch feedback by page.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Ask clients to review one page at a time rather than clicking around randomly. It keeps the task board organized and helps developers work in focused blocks.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
